{
    "publish_date": "2012-12-05T16:21:54.000Z", 
    "video_length": "PT3M51S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "We all start life as one single cell.", 
            "dur": "2.946", 
            "start": "14.359"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Then that cell divides and we are two cells,", 
            "dur": "2.651", 
            "start": "17.305"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "then four,", 
            "dur": "0.824", 
            "start": "19.956"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "then eight.", 
            "dur": "1.075", 
            "start": "20.78"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Cells form tissues,", 
            "dur": "1.102", 
            "start": "21.855"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "tissues form organs,", 
            "dur": "1.176", 
            "start": "22.957"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "organs form us.", 
            "dur": "1.925", 
            "start": "24.133"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "These cell divisions, by which we go from a single cell", 
            "dur": "2.949", 
            "start": "26.058"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to 100 trillion cells,", 
            "dur": "1.867", 
            "start": "29.007"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "are called growth.", 
            "dur": "2.101", 
            "start": "30.874"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And growth seems like a simple thing", 
            "dur": "1.654", 
            "start": "32.975"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "because when we think of it,", 
            "dur": "1.34", 
            "start": "34.629"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we typically think of someone getting taller", 
            "dur": "2.26", 
            "start": "35.969"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or, later in life, wider,", 
            "dur": "2.148", 
            "start": "38.229"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but to cells, growth isn&#39;t simple.", 
            "dur": "2.498", 
            "start": "40.377"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Cell division is an intricate chemical dance", 
            "dur": "2.449", 
            "start": "42.875"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that&#39;s part individual, part community-driven.", 
            "dur": "2.631", 
            "start": "45.324"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And in a neighborhood of 100 trillion cells,", 
            "dur": "2.525", 
            "start": "47.955"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "some times things go wrong.", 
            "dur": "2.524", 
            "start": "50.48"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Maybe an individual cell&#39;s set of instructions, or DNA,", 
            "dur": "3.704", 
            "start": "53.004"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "gets a typo,", 
            "dur": "1.139", 
            "start": "56.708"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "what we call a mutation.", 
            "dur": "1.857", 
            "start": "57.847"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Most of the time, the cell senses mistakes", 
            "dur": "1.858", 
            "start": "59.704"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and shuts itself down,", 
            "dur": "1.834", 
            "start": "61.562"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or the system detects a troublemaker", 
            "dur": "1.566", 
            "start": "63.396"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and eliminates it.", 
            "dur": "1.007", 
            "start": "64.962"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But, enough mutations can bypass the fail-safes,", 
            "dur": "2.844", 
            "start": "65.969"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "driving the cell to divide recklessly.", 
            "dur": "2.154", 
            "start": "68.813"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That one rogue cell becomes two,", 
            "dur": "2.166", 
            "start": "70.967"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "then four,", 
            "dur": "0.992", 
            "start": "73.133"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "then eight.", 
            "dur": "1.254", 
            "start": "74.125"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "At every stage, the incorrect instructions", 
            "dur": "1.735", 
            "start": "75.379"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "are passed along to the cells&#39; offspring.", 
            "dur": "2.476", 
            "start": "77.114"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Weeks, months, or years", 
            "dur": "1.866", 
            "start": "79.59"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "after that one rogue cell transformed,", 
            "dur": "2.644", 
            "start": "81.456"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you might see your doctor about a lump in your breast.", 
            "dur": "2.5", 
            "start": "84.1"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Difficulty going to the bathroom could reveal", 
            "dur": "1.756", 
            "start": "86.6"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a problem in your intestine,", 
            "dur": "2.001", 
            "start": "88.356"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "prostate,", 
            "dur": "0.372", 
            "start": "90.357"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or bladder.", 
            "dur": "0.799", 
            "start": "90.729"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Or, a routine blood test might count too many white cells", 
            "dur": "3.317", 
            "start": "91.528"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or elevated liver enzymes.", 
            "dur": "2.185", 
            "start": "94.845"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Your doctor delivers the bad news:", 
            "dur": "2.008", 
            "start": "97.03"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it&#39;s cancer.", 
            "dur": "1.123", 
            "start": "99.038"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "From here your strategy will depend", 
            "dur": "1.298", 
            "start": "100.161"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "on where the cancer is and", 
            "dur": "1.907", 
            "start": "101.459"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "how far it&#39;s progressed.", 
            "dur": "1.682", 
            "start": "103.366"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If the tumor is slow-growing and in one place,", 
            "dur": "2.648", 
            "start": "105.048"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "surgery might be all you need, if anything.", 
            "dur": "2.401", 
            "start": "107.696"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If the tumor is fast-growing or invading nearby tissue,", 
            "dur": "2.944", 
            "start": "110.097"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "your doctor might recommend radiation", 
            "dur": "2.129", 
            "start": "113.041"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or surgery followed by radiation.", 
            "dur": "2.786", 
            "start": "115.17"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If the cancer has spread,", 
            "dur": "1.208", 
            "start": "117.956"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or if it&#39;s inherently everywhere like a leukemia,", 
            "dur": "2.593", 
            "start": "119.164"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "your doctor will most likely recommend chemotherapy", 
            "dur": "3.116", 
            "start": "121.757"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or a combination of radiation and chemo.", 
            "dur": "2.385", 
            "start": "124.873"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Radiation and most forms of chemo work", 
            "dur": "1.941", 
            "start": "127.258"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "by physically shredding the cells&#39; DNA", 
            "dur": "2.328", 
            "start": "129.199"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or disrupting the copying machinery.", 
            "dur": "3.005", 
            "start": "131.527"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But neither radiation nor chemotherapeutic drugs target only cancer cells.", 
            "dur": "4.562", 
            "start": "134.532"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Radiation hits whatever you point it at,", 
            "dur": "2.469", 
            "start": "139.094"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and your blood stream carries chemo-therapeutics", 
            "dur": "2.022", 
            "start": "141.563"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "all over your body.", 
            "dur": "1.989", 
            "start": "143.585"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, what happens when different cells get hit?", 
            "dur": "2.942", 
            "start": "145.574"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s look at a healthy liver cell,", 
            "dur": "1.479", 
            "start": "148.516"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a healthy hair cell,", 
            "dur": "1.253", 
            "start": "149.995"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and a cancerous cell.", 
            "dur": "1.753", 
            "start": "151.248"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The healthy liver cell divides only when it is stressed;", 
            "dur": "2.845", 
            "start": "153.001"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the healthy hair cell divides frequently;", 
            "dur": "2.103", 
            "start": "155.846"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and the cancer cell divides even more frequently and recklessly.", 
            "dur": "3.928", 
            "start": "157.949"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "When you take a chemotherapeutic drug,", 
            "dur": "1.752", 
            "start": "161.877"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it will hit all of these cells.", 
            "dur": "2.452", 
            "start": "163.629"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And remember that the drugs work typically by disrupting cell division.", 
            "dur": "3.398", 
            "start": "166.081"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, every time a cell divides,", 
            "dur": "1.715", 
            "start": "169.479"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it opens itself up to attack,", 
            "dur": "2.535", 
            "start": "171.194"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and that means the more frequently a cell divides,", 
            "dur": "1.821", 
            "start": "173.729"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the more likely the drug is to kill it.", 
            "dur": "2.495", 
            "start": "175.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, remember that hair cell?", 
            "dur": "1.649", 
            "start": "178.045"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It divides frequently and isn&#39;t a threat.", 
            "dur": "3.226", 
            "start": "179.694"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And, there are other frequently dividing cells in your body", 
            "dur": "2.382", 
            "start": "182.92"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "like skin cells, gut cells, and blood cells.", 
            "dur": "3.164", 
            "start": "185.302"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So the list of unpleasant side effects of cancer treatment", 
            "dur": "2.631", 
            "start": "188.466"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "parallels these tissue types:", 
            "dur": "2.031", 
            "start": "191.097"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "hair loss,", 
            "dur": "0.575", 
            "start": "193.128"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "skin rashes,", 
            "dur": "1.028", 
            "start": "193.703"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "nausea,", 
            "dur": "0.563", 
            "start": "194.731"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "vomiting,", 
            "dur": "0.588", 
            "start": "195.294"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "fatigue,", 
            "dur": "0.583", 
            "start": "195.882"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "weight loss,", 
            "dur": "0.831", 
            "start": "196.465"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and pain.", 
            "dur": "1.387", 
            "start": "197.296"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That makes sense because these are the cells that get hit the hardest.", 
            "dur": "3.65", 
            "start": "198.683"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, in the end, it is all about growth.", 
            "dur": "2.545", 
            "start": "202.333"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Cancer hijacks cells&#39; natural division machinery", 
            "dur": "2.391", 
            "start": "204.878"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and forces them to put the pedal to the metal,", 
            "dur": "2.549", 
            "start": "207.269"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "growing rapidly and recklessly.", 
            "dur": "2.134", 
            "start": "209.818"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But, using chemotherapeutic drugs,", 
            "dur": "1.75", 
            "start": "211.952"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we take advantage of that aggressiveness,", 
            "dur": "2.424", 
            "start": "213.702"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and we turn cancer&#39;s main strength", 
            "dur": "1.577", 
            "start": "216.126"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "into a weakness.", 
            "dur": "2.488", 
            "start": "217.703"
        }
    ], 
